ers, for Jan believes cooking is about competition and Kiriko believes cooking is about heart.\\\",\\\"averageScore\\\":67,\\\"popularity\\\":6418,\\\"episodes\\\":null,\\\"duration\\\":23,\\\"genres\\\":[\\\"Action\\\",\\\"Comedy\\\"],\\\"format\\\":\\\"TV\\\",\\\"season\\\":\\\"SUMMER\\\",\\\"seasonYear\\\":2026,\\\"status\\\":\\\"RELEASING\\\",\\\"nextAiringEpisode\\\":{\\\"episode\\\":3,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784449800},\\\"trailer\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"awvmDnz3URo\\\",\\\"site\\\":\\\"youtube\\\",\\\"thumbnail\\\":\\\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/awvmDnz3URo/hqdefault.jpg\\\"},\\\"isAdult\\\":false}},{\\\"id\\\":416916,\\\"episode\\\":375,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784451600,\\\"media\\\":{\\\"id\\\":118123,\\\"title\\\":{\\\"romaji\\\":\\\"Holo no Graffiti\\\",\\\"english\\\":null,\\\"native\\\":\\\"ホロのぐらふぃてぃ\\\"},\\\"coverImage\\\":{\\\"extraLarge\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx118123-xqn5fYsjKXJU.png\\\",\\\"large\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx118123-xqn5fYsjKXJU.png\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"#e4ae5d\\\"},\\\"bannerImage\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/118123-BvHyzWd850nZ.jpg\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"From unraveling the secrets of opening and closing doors to defusing surprise packages more commonly known as bombs, there is never a dull day at the Hololive Production office! \\u003ci\\u003eHolo no Graffiti\\u003c/i\\u003e follows an eccentric cast of Virtual YouTubers, also known as \\\\\\\"VTubers,\\\\\\\" going about their absurd yet hilarious daily lives, detailing all their cute moments and mishaps.\\\\n\\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003e\\\\n(Source: MAL Rewrite)\\\",\\\"averageScore\\\":78,\\\"popularity\\\":14420,\\\"episodes\\\":null,\\\"duration\\\":2,\\\"genres\\\":[\\\"Action\\\",\\\"Adventure\\\",\\\"Comedy\\\"],\\\"format\\\":\\\"ONA\\\",\\\"season\\\":\\\"SPRING\\\",\\\"seasonYear\\\":2019,\\\"status\\\":\\\"RELEASING\\\",\\\"nextAiringEpisode\\\":{\\\"episode\\\":375,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784451600},\\\"trailer\\\":null,\\\"isAdult\\\":false}},{\\\"id\\\":394981,\\\"episode\\\":2841,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784453400,\\\"media\\\":{\\\"id\\\":2406,\\\"title\\\":{\\\"romaji\\\":\\\"Sazae-san\\\",\\\"english\\\":null,\\\"native\\\":\\\"サザエさん\\\"},\\\"coverImage\\\":{\\\"extraLarge\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx2406-nP8NIct9Sci3.jpg\\\",\\\"large\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx2406-nP8NIct9Sci3.jpg\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"#f1bb43\\\"},\\\"bannerImage\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/2406-ROqXxejQ5bH9.jpg\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The main character is a mother named Sazae-san. She lives in a house with her husband, her kid, her siblings and her parents. The show is the ultimate family program and tends to follow traditional themes. Think of this show as the Japanese equivalent to \\\\\\\"The Partridge Family\\\\\\\" and you'll get a good feel for this show's atmosphere. Don't expect to see things like violence, swearing, kung-fu action or magical girls. The plots are more like \\\\\\\"Today, Sazae-san goes to the new mall and gets lost\\\\\\\". Such \\\\\\\"boring\\\\\\\" plotlines and the simplistic art are often a turn-off to non-Japanese audiences, but most Japanese find the show incredibly good. As a result, it continues to be one of the top ratings grabbers on TV and is one of the few anime that is considered \\\\\\\"acceptable\\\\\\\" by adults.\\\",\\\"averageScore\\\":55,\\\"popularity\\\":2459,\\\"episodes\\\":null,\\\"duration\\\":24,\\\"genres\\\":[\\\"Comedy\\\",\\\"Slice of Life\\\"],\\\"format\\\":\\\"TV\\\",\\\"season\\\":\\\"FALL\\\",\\\"seasonYear\\\":1969,\\\"status\\\":\\\"RELEASING\\\",\\\"nextAiringEpisode\\\":{\\\"episode\\\":2841,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784453400},\\\"trailer\\\":null,\\\"isAdult\\\":false}},{\\\"id\\\":413669,\\\"episode\\\":3,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784466000,\\\"media\\\":{\\\"id\\\":198409,\\\"title\\\":{\\\"romaji\\\":\\\"Sekai Saikyou no Kouei: Meikyuukoku no Shinjin Tansakusha\\\",\\\"english\\\":\\\"The World's Strongest Rearguard\\\",\\\"native\\\":\\\"世界最強の後衛 ～迷宮国の新人探索者～\\\"},\\\"coverImage\\\":{\\\"extraLarge\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx198409-EiWJXfYnvfu4.png\\\",\\\"large\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx198409-EiWJXfYnvfu4.png\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"#0dbbfe\\\"},\\\"bannerImage\\\":null,\\\"description\\\":\\\"After a fatal accident, overworked office worker Arihito Atobe is reborn in the Labyrinth Country as a Seeker with the rare Rearguard class—an all-purpose support role that excels in attack, defense, and healing. Joined by a fierce demi-human mercenary and his former boss, Arihito dives into deadly dungeons and rises through the ranks. The adventure of the strongest support class begins!\\\\n\\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003e\\\\n(Source: Crunchyroll)\\\",\\\"averageScore\\\":59,\\\"popularity\\\":17962,\\\"episodes\\\":12,\\\"duration\\\":24,\\\"genres\\\":[\\\"Action\\\",\\\"Adventure\\\",\\\"Fantasy\\\"],\\\"format\\\":\\\"TV\\\",\\\"season\\\":\\\"SUMMER\\\",\\\"seasonYear\\\":2026,\\\"status\\\":\\\"RELEASING\\\",\\\"nextAiringEpisode\\\":{\\\"episode\\\":3,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784466000},\\\"trailer\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"vdJo_3uZ92s\\\",\\\"site\\\":\\\"youtube\\\",\\\"thumbnail\\\":\\\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vdJo_3uZ92s/hqdefault.jpg\\\"},\\\"isAdult\\\":false}},{\\\"id\\\":414988,\\\"episode\\\":3,\\\"airingAt\\\":1784467800,\\\"media\\\":{\\\"id\\\":200637,\\\"title\\\":{\\\"romaji\\\":\\\"Kimi no Koto ga Dai Dai Dai Dai Daisuki na 100-nin no Kanojo 3rd Season\\\",\\\"english\\\":\\\"The 100 Girlfriends Who Really, Really, Really, Really, REALLY Love You Season 3\\\",\\\"native\\\":\\\"君のことが大大大大大好きな100人の彼女 第3期\\\"},\\\"coverImage\\\":{\\\"extraLarge\\\":\\\"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx200637-QLR5uv9SbQ69.jpg\\